The paper proposes a clustering algorithm that has wide applications in various fields, including bioinformatics and astronomy. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper's focus on discovering nonspherical clusters also aligns with the topics covered in these sub-categories.
